<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Maldoror</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Greetings. I am hearing all sorts of rumors on the damage this skil does when a cleric has it maxed out to the third skill level. Can anyone give me a rough idea on its damage output? Ive heard at third level, its a fear and dot that does anywhere from 6k to 10k damage if the dot runs its course. <P>Sorry if this question has been answered already; didnt see any specific comments on it when I tried to search past threads. Thanks for your time and help!<P>------------------<BR><B>Seveian</B><BR><A HREF="http://www.reconstructed.nu" TARGET=_blank>Reconstructed Officer</A><BR>Eci Server<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2782" TARGET=_blank>Magelo</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Arturo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">1st level - Fear/Dot 2k<BR>2nd level - Fear/Dot 5k<BR>3rd level - Fear/Dot 10k<P>------------------<BR>Arturo Fuente<BR>Venerable Priest of Mithaniel Marr<BR><A HREF="http://24.25.18.10/" TARGET=_blank>Circle of Legends</A><BR>Bristlebane<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=114197" TARGET=_blank>Arturo's Profile</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Weird Pete</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sounds about right to me.<P>------------------<BR>Canton<BR>Cleric of the 4th Season<P>Hoody Hoo!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">By-Tor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If it added a snare componant we could equal druids.<BR> <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/tongue.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Clenzz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">what i want to know is.....<P><BR>Say lvl 3 does 10K.  since it's a DOT, and DOTs are supposed to be less if the mobs moving, would it do more damage if ya rooted the mobs while it's hitting them? =)<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=109801" TARGET=_blank>Clenzz Teveril</A><BR> <A HREF="http://www.enlighteneddark.org" TARGET=_blank>www.enlighteneddark.org</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Atro</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">DoT damage is only reduced if they are chasing you, if they are fleeing (feared low hp) it SHOULD do full damage.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Daanya</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">First level:<BR>1000 damage (not 2000) over 24 seconds<BR>2.5 cast time<BR>24 second fear<P>Second level:<BR>5000 damage over 24 seconds<BR>5.0 cast time<BR>24 second fear<P>Third level:<BR>10000 damage over 24 seconds<BR>7.5 cast time<BR>24 second fear<P>Which, of course, doesn't make it particularly useful unfortunately as the best you could do would be level 3 in grey at level 59 (having BAotR). Get up jboots / run 3 and pull as many Shissars / skeles as you can. Take the next 2 minutes trying to get them all near each other then stand back and wait for them to come in.<P>Lose probably at least a bub of health when they reach you, take a step forward to be in the thick of them. Cast Stun Command and pray none resist.<P>You have 9 seconds so start Turn Undead and it should land about a second before stun wears off.<P>So every 72 minutes you can kill probably 10 or so (more is begging for the 1 resist it takes to interrupt TU and cause you to die waiting for SC to refresh).<P>Or, you can make a paladin, get Slay 3. Return to Grey and several times during the previous 72 minutes land a crit for just about as much as they have health (Snakes have bout 5k hp).<P>Run 3, Wisdom 3-5, SCM 3, MC 3, MGB. That's the maximum a cleric will ever need. The rest is complete fluff. It's why I did make a paladin and he will be getting Slay someday. Only 7 levels away until I go 100% AA exp  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aean</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">hmmmmmmm<BR>this gave me an idea <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif">  lets say you have an entire group of clerics, each with level 3 TU and you do what you guys are saying about pulling the undead snakes and smacking them all with this you could then do one massive pull every 12 minutes with little pulls in between. Maybe add a pally or two into the group instead and just hunt undead all night <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Artemi</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Is it unresistable? Can it work on rooted mobs? Am asking this because many boss mobs in Akheva Ruins are undead and perma rooted.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
